import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='country', y='counts', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['latitude'])
    sns.scatterplot(x='latitude', y=data.groupby('latitude').size().index, size=data.groupby('latitude').size().values, sizes=(10, 200), legend=False)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.axvline(x=data['latitude'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['latitude'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name_length'] = data['name'].apply(lambda x: len(x))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='name_length', bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['name_length'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["name_length"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
